--TEST--
Filter list entry matching direct dependency preventing a successful update.
--COMPOSER--
{
    "name": "acme/project",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "require": {
        "acme/library": "1.0.0"
    },
    "repositories": [
        {
            "type": "package",
            "package": [
                {
                    "name": "acme/library",
                    "version": "1.0.0",
                    "source": { "reference": "some.branch", "type": "git", "url": "" }
                }
            ],
            "filter": {
                "test-list": [
                    {
                        "package": "acme/library",
                        "constraint": "*",
                        "category": "malware",
                        "url": "https://example.org/malware/acme/library"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}
--RUN--
update -v

--EXPECT-EXIT-CODE--
2

--EXPECT-OUTPUT--
Loading composer repositories with package information
Updating dependencies
Your requirements could not be resolved to an installable set of packages.

  Problem 1
    - Root composer.json requires acme/library 1.0.0 (exact version match: 1.0.0 or 1.0.0.0), found acme/library[1.0.0] but these were not loaded, because they were flagged as malware by test-list (see https://example.org/malware/acme/library). To ignore filters for this package, add the package to the "filter.don-filter-packages" config. To turn the feature off entirely, you can set "filter" to false.

--EXPECT--
